channel.title: UGRENT: Computer Hardware Issue help
channel.description:
Ok so my secondary computer won't boot (I press the power button, no go nothing happens) I tried support which people are as dumb 10 year old kids who knows basically nothing about computers. Would could this be caused by? On the MoBo, the power LED is on when the PSU is plugged. At the begging of my attempts to boot my computer, the fans was on for only about 20 milliseconds, then its basically none. Could this be my PSU? My MoBo? Or my CPU? Help is greatly appreciated. Thanks
PSU= Power Supply Unit MoBo=Motherboard CPU=Central Processing Unit Support= Dumbass kids :P

item.title: UGRENT: Computer Hardware Issue help
item.dc:creator: @Coolnoob55 Coolnoob55
item.description:
@Coolnoob55 wrote:

[quote=“d3ltr33, post:8, topic:3367”]why not take the psu from your other computer and stick it in the broken one and see if it works? If not… then atleast you know it’s not the PSU that’s screwed[/quote] Well because the PSU from my secondary is only like a crappy 305 watt one for Micro-ATX boards while my main is a pretty decent aspire 600w ATX power supply. I’m very sure that the 305 watt will not be able to support it. On second thought, I believe I’m still under warranty, except I would have to find that stupid receipt =(

item.title: UGRENT: Computer Hardware Issue help
item.dc:creator: @hellothere hellothere
item.description:
@hellothere wrote:

I’d say do what they’ll do at the supply shop. Get yourself a new power supply and test, if thats not it return it and get a refund, then try motherboard and repeat until you solve your problem. I’d go for motherboard and processor last. And most likely its not your bios.

item.dc:creator: @Zach1188 Zach1188
item.description:
@Zach1188 wrote:

It most likely is not your motherboard or power supply, as the fans turn on. I can’t really tell, but I would assume it’s your bios or CPU. I cannot be sure, however, as I would have to look at it in person. The only advice I can really give you is to take it to a repair shop.
